-- Koc's second-quarter net rises 49 percent to 872.4 million lira
-- 
-- Fri Aug 15, 2014 01:01AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 15 (Reuters) - Koc Holding <KCHOL.IS>, Turkey's biggest company, said on Monday its second-quarter net income rose 49 percent to 872.4 million lira ($40.5 million).

Sales in the period were 16.5 billion lira, Koc said in an income statement to the Istanbul stock exchange.